<a name = "vie"><b> Residue Theorem </b></a>
<p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Let $f(z)$ be holomorphic in and on a simple, closed,
			positively-oriented (roughly, CCW) curve $C$
			except for possibly finitely many isolated singularities
			inside $C$. Then
			\[
				\oint_{C} f(z)dz =  2\pi i\sum_{n=1}^N \text{Res}(f(z);z_n),
			\]
			where $z_1, z_2, \ldots, z_N$ are the isolated singularities
			of $f(z)$ inside $C$.
		</li>
		<ul>
			<li>
				Proof idea: Use our VIE.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</ul>
</p>